[normal]Written evidence submitted by Marine Conservation Society[bold]&#xa0;[bold]Th
[normal]e Marine Conservation Society (
[normal]MCS) is the 
[normal]UK
[normal] charity dedicated to the protection of the 
[normal]UK
[normal]’s seas, shores and wildlife. 
[normal]MCS
[normal] campaigns for clean seas and beaches, sustainable fisheries, protection of marine life and their habitats, and the sensitive use of our marine resources for future generations. 
[normal]MCS
[normal] produces the annual Good Beach Guide, the Good Fish Guide on sustainable seafood, organises volunteer projects and surveys such as 
[normal]Beachwatch
[normal], the 
[normal]Beachwatch
[normal] Big Weekend and Basking Shark Watch and works closely with the UK Government and devolved administrations on the development and implementation of marine laws and policies.
[normal]MCS is a core member of the Break the 
[normal]B
[normal]ag 
[normal]H
[normal]abit coalition that
[normal] includes The Campaign to Protect Rural England, Keep Britain Tidy, Surfers Against Sewage, Thames 21 and Greener upon Thames. The coalition 
[normal]has been campaigning for a charge on all single use carrier bags.  
